11/09/2006
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Foreign Minister Mladen Ivanic announced on Sunday (10 September) that BiH would officially establish diplomatic ties with Montenegro very soon. He told reporters in Banja Luka that the bilateral agreement on launching diplomatic relations has been drafted and the two sides must now schedule a date for signing. As soon as the document is sealed, BiH would open an embassy in Podgorica, he said. (NTV Hayat, RTRS - 10/09/06)
